$ /usr/share

`/usr/share` contains subdirectories with specific application data that can be shared among different architectures of the same OS.

sa:
 `→ Linux/fhs/usr/share/applications`

 `→ Linux/fhs/usr/share/cups`

 `→ Linux/fhs/usr/share/distro-info`

 `→ Linux/fhs/usr/share/doc`

 `→ Linux/fhs/usr/share/hwdata`

 `→ Linux/fhs/usr/share/icons`

 `→ Linux/fhs/usr/share/mime`

 `→ Linux/fhs/usr/share/man`: the directory for → Linux/man-page[man pages].

 `→ Linux/fhs/usr/share/misc`

 `→ Linux/fhs/usr/share/pixmaps`

 `→ Linux/fhs/usr/share/pkgconfig`

 `→ Linux/fhs/usr/share/ppd`

 `→ Linux/fhs/usr/share/terminfo`

 `→ Linux/fhs/usr/share/xml`

 `→ Linux/fhs/usr/share/xsessions`

  → Linux/fhs
